gr.interamerican.bo2.utils.meta.descriptors
Interface PropertyDefinition

All Superinterfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public interface PropertyDefinition
extends java.io.Serializable

A PropertyDefinition object has all the necessary information for the creation of a BoPropertyDescriptor.
name: Property name.
readOnly: The value of the property is read-only.
hasDefault: The value of the property has a default value.
defaultValue: The default value of the property (if applicable).
zeroAllowed: The property value may be zero (applicable for Number sub-types).
negativeAllowed: The property value may be negative (applicable for most Number sub-types). nullAllowed: The property value may be null.
minLength: Minimum length of property value string representation.
maxLength: Maximum length of property value string representation.
integerLength: Maximum length of property value integer digits (applicable for Number sub-types). The corresponding minimum value is implicitly considered to be 0.
decimalLength: Maximum length of property value decimal digits (applicable for some Number sub-types). The corresponding minimum value is implicitly considered to be 0.
listCd: Code of system list that the value for this property is cached into (if applicable).
subListCd: Code of system sub-list that the value for this property is cached into (if applicable).
cacheName: Name of the cache that the value of this property is cached to (if applicable).
expression: A regular expression that can validate the value of the property.
